"""
ONE-SHOT TIME SERIES PIPELINE (AirPassengers)
- Loads dataset
- Visualizes series + year/month boxplots
- Log transform + moving average smoothing
- Seasonal decomposition (additive + multiplicative)
- Stationarity tests (ADF + KPSS)
- Detrend + deseasonalize (demo)
- ACF/PACF + lag plots
- Forecastability (Approx Entropy + Sample Entropy)
- (Optional) Granger causality using 'year' as exogenous
- Train/Test split
- Fit ARIMA and SARIMA (SARIMAX in statsmodels)
- Forecast + evaluation (RMSE, MAPE)
"""

import warnings
warnings.filterwarnings("ignore")
from statsmodels.tools.sm_exceptions import InterpolationWarning
warnings.filterwarnings("ignore", category=InterpolationWarning)

import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

from datetime import datetime
from scipy import signal
from statsmodels.tsa.seasonal import seasonal_decompose
from statsmodels.tsa.stattools import adfuller, kpss, grangercausalitytests
from statsmodels.graphics.tsaplots import plot_acf, plot_pacf
from pandas.plotting import lag_plot

from statsmodels.tsa.statespace.sarimax import SARIMAX

plt.rcParams.update({'figure.figsize': (12, 6), 'figure.dpi': 120})

# -----------------------------
# 1) LOAD DATA
# -----------------------------
url = "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/swapnilsaurav/Dataset/master/AirPassengers.csv"
df = pd.read_csv(url, parse_dates=["Month"])
df = df.sort_values("Month").reset_index(drop=True)

# Create time index
df.set_index("Month", inplace=True)
ts = df["#Passengers"].asfreq("MS")  # Monthly Start frequency

print("Dataset head:\n", ts.head(), "\n")
print("Data range:", ts.index.min().date(), "to", ts.index.max().date())
print("Missing values:", ts.isna().sum())

# -----------------------------

plt.figure()

plt.show()

# Year-wise and Month-wise boxplots (without seaborn, using pandas + matplotlib)
df_box = df.copy()

df_box["month"] = df_box.index.strftime("%b")

# Year-wise boxplot
plt.figure(figsize=(14, 5), dpi=120)

plt.title("Year-wise Box Plot (Trend)")

plt.figure(figsize=(14, 5), dpi=120)
df_box.loc[mask].boxplot(column="#Passengers", by="month", grid=False)

plt.plot(moving_avg, label="12-month rolling mean")

# 4) DECOMPOSITION (LOG SERIES)
# -----------------------------
decomp_log = seasonal_decompose(ts_log, model="additive", period=12)

plt.figure(figsize=(12, 8), dpi=120)

plt.subplot(414); plt.plot(resid_log);   plt.title("Residual")
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

# Additive vs Multiplicative decomposition on original scale
result_mul = seasonal_decompose(ts, model="multiplicative", period=12, extrapolate_trend="freq")
result_add = seasonal_decompose(ts, model="additive", period=12, extrapolate_trend="freq")

result_mul.plot()
plt.suptitle("Multiplicative Decomposition", y=1.02)
plt.show()

result_add.plot()
plt.suptitle("Additive Decomposition", y=1.02)

# Reconstructed components (multiplicative)
df_reconstructed = pd.concat([result_mul.seasonal, result_mul.trend, result_mul.resid, result_mul.observed], axis=1)
df_reconstructed.columns = ["seas", "trend", "resid", "actual_values"]
print("Reconstructed data (multiplicative) head:\n", df_reconstructed.head(), "\n")

# -----------------------------
# 5) STATIONARITY TESTS (ADF + KPSS)
# -----------------------------
def stationarity_tests(series, name="series"):
    series = series.dropna()

    # ADF: H0 = non-stationary (unit root)
    adf = adfuller(series, autolag="AIC")
    adf_stat, adf_p = adf[0], adf[1]

    # KPSS: H0 = stationary (trend or level depends on regression)
    kps = kpss(series, regression="c", nlags="auto")
    kps_stat, kps_p = kps[0], kps[1]

    print(f"--- Stationarity Tests: {name} ---")
    print(f"ADF  Statistic: {adf_stat:.4f}, p-value: {adf_p:.6f}  (p<0.05 => stationary)")
    print(f"KPSS Statistic: {kps_stat:.4f}, p-value: {kps_p:.6f}  (p<0.05 => non-stationary)")
    print("ADF Critical Values:", {k: round(v, 4) for k, v in adf[4].items()})
    print("KPSS Critical Values:", {k: round(v, 4) for k, v in kps[3].items()})
    print()

stationarity_tests(ts, "Original")
stationarity_tests(ts_log, "Log")
stationarity_tests(ts_log.diff(1), "Log Diff(1)")
stationarity_tests(ts_log.diff(12), "Log Seasonal Diff(12)")
stationarity_tests(ts_log.diff(1).diff(12), "Log Diff(1) + Seasonal Diff(12)")

# -----------------------------
# 8) FORECASTABILITY (ApEn + SampEn)
# -----------------------------
def ApEn(U, m, r):
    """Approximate entropy"""
    U = np.array(U, dtype=float)
    N = len(U)

    def _maxdist(x_i, x_j):
        return np.max(np.abs(x_i - x_j))

    def _phi(mm):
        x = np.array([U[i:i+mm] for i in range(N - mm + 1)])
        C = []
        for x_i in x:
            C.append(np.mean([_maxdist(x_i, x_j) <= r for x_j in x]))
        return np.mean(np.log(np.array(C) + 1e-12))

    return abs(_phi(m + 1) - _phi(m))

def SampEn(U, m, r):
    """Sample entropy"""
    U = np.array(U, dtype=float)
    N = len(U)

    def _maxdist(x_i, x_j):
        return np.max(np.abs(x_i - x_j))

    def _count(mm):
        x = np.array([U[i:i+mm] for i in range(N - mm + 1)])
        count = 0
        total = 0
        for i in range(len(x)):
            for j in range(len(x)):
                if i == j:
                    continue
                total += 1
                if _maxdist(x[i], x[j]) <= r:
                    count += 1
        return count, total

    c1, t1 = _count(m)
    c2, t2 = _count(m + 1)
    return -np.log((c2 / (t2 + 1e-12)) / (c1 / (t1 + 1e-12)) + 1e-12)

apen = ApEn(ts.values, m=2, r=0.2*np.std(ts.values))
sampen = SampEn(ts.values, m=2, r=0.2*np.std(ts.values))
print(f"Approximate Entropy (ApEn): {apen:.6f}  (higher => harder to forecast)")
print(f"Sample Entropy (SampEn):   {sampen:.6f}  (higher => harder to forecast)\n")

# -----------------------------
# 9) (OPTIONAL) GRANGER CAUSALITY: 'year' as exogenous
# NOTE: purely illustrative; year is deterministic with time.
# -----------------------------
df_gc = pd.DataFrame({"Passengers": ts.values, "year": ts.index.year}, index=ts.index)
print("Granger Causality Test (Passengers ~ year) up to 2 lags:")
grangercausalitytests(df_gc[["Passengers", "year"]], maxlag=2, verbose=True)
print()

# -----------------------------
# 10) TRAIN / TEST SPLIT
# -----------------------------
horizon = 24  # forecast 24 months (2 years)
train = ts.iloc[:-horizon]
test = ts.iloc[-horizon:]

plt.figure()
plt.plot(train, label="Train")
plt.plot(test, label="Test")
plt.title("Train/Test Split")
plt.xlabel("Month")
plt.ylabel("Passengers")
plt.legend()
plt.show()

def rmse(y_true, y_pred):
    y_true = np.array(y_true, dtype=float)
    y_pred = np.array(y_pred, dtype=float)
    return np.sqrt(np.mean((y_true - y_pred)**2))

def mape(y_true, y_pred):
    y_true = np.array(y_true, dtype=float)
    y_pred = np.array(y_pred, dtype=float)
    return np.mean(np.abs((y_true - y_pred) / (y_true + 1e-12))) * 100

# -----------------------------
# 11) MODEL 1: ARIMA (via SARIMAX without seasonality)
# -----------------------------
# We'll model on log scale to stabilize variance, then invert with exp.
train_log = np.log(train)
test_log = np.log(test)

arima_order = (1, 1, 1)  # simple default; you can tune based on ACF/PACF
model_arima = SARIMAX(train_log, order=arima_order, seasonal_order=(0, 0, 0, 0),
                      enforce_stationarity=False, enforce_invertibility=False)
res_arima = model_arima.fit(disp=False)

pred_arima_log = res_arima.get_forecast(steps=horizon).predicted_mean
pred_arima = np.exp(pred_arima_log)

arima_rmse = rmse(test.values, pred_arima.values)
arima_mape = mape(test.values, pred_arima.values)

print(f"ARIMA{arima_order}  -> RMSE: {arima_rmse:.3f}, MAPE: {arima_mape:.2f}%")

plt.figure()
plt.plot(train, label="Train")
plt.plot(test, label="Test")
plt.plot(pred_arima, label="ARIMA Forecast")
plt.title(f"ARIMA Forecast (RMSE={arima_rmse:.2f}, MAPE={arima_mape:.2f}%)")
plt.xlabel("Month")
plt.ylabel("Passengers")
plt.legend()
plt.show()

# -----------------------------
# 12) MODEL 2: SARIMA (Seasonal ARIMA via SARIMAX)
# -----------------------------
# AirPassengers is monthly with strong yearly seasonality => seasonal period m=12
sarima_order = (1, 1, 1)
seasonal_order = (1, 1, 1, 12)

model_sarima = SARIMAX(train_log, order=sarima_order, seasonal_order=seasonal_order,
                       enforce_stationarity=False, enforce_invertibility=False)
res_sarima = model_sarima.fit(disp=False)

pred_sarima_log = res_sarima.get_forecast(steps=horizon).predicted_mean
pred_sarima = np.exp(pred_sarima_log)

sarima_rmse = rmse(test.values, pred_sarima.values)
sarima_mape = mape(test.values, pred_sarima.values)

print(f"SARIMA{sarima_order}x{seasonal_order} -> RMSE: {sarima_rmse:.3f}, MAPE: {sarima_mape:.2f}%")

plt.figure()
plt.plot(train, label="Train")
plt.plot(test, label="Test")
plt.plot(pred_sarima, label="SARIMA Forecast")
plt.title(f"SARIMA Forecast (RMSE={sarima_rmse:.2f}, MAPE={sarima_mape:.2f}%)")
plt.xlabel("Month")
plt.ylabel("Passengers")
plt.legend()
plt.show()

# -----------------------------
# 13) EXTENDED FORECAST (FULL DATA -> NEXT 24 MONTHS)
# -----------------------------
full_log = np.log(ts)

final_model = SARIMAX(full_log, order=sarima_order, seasonal_order=seasonal_order,
                      enforce_stationarity=False, enforce_invertibility=False)
final_res = final_model.fit(disp=False)

future_steps = 24
future_forecast_log = final_res.get_forecast(steps=future_steps).predicted_mean
future_forecast = np.exp(future_forecast_log)

plt.figure()
plt.plot(ts, label="Observed")
plt.plot(future_forecast, label="Next 24 months Forecast")
plt.title("Final Model Forecast (Next 24 Months)")
plt.xlabel("Month")
plt.ylabel("Passengers")
plt.legend()
plt.show()

print("\nNext 24 months forecast (head):")
print(future_forecast.head())
